Tim Ward and his wife Brandy were at home in Oso, Washington, on March 22, 2014 when tons of debris, soil and rock came crashing down from upland .
The mudslide killed their turkeys, chickens and four canines, but only one of their five dogs survived .
A donor has now donated $360,000 to pay for the mortgage .
Tim said: 'There are still good Samaritans out there. This is life-changing'